context: Ireland developed a strong middle class, especially in the major cities, by the <a0_0><b5_0>mid-nineteenth century<b5_0/>.<a0_0/> They were active patrons of department stores. <a1_0><b6_0>Delany's New Mart<b6_0/><a1_0/> was opened in 1853 in <a2_0><b7_0>Dublin<b7_0/><a2_0/>, Ireland. Unlike others, Delany's had not evolved gradually from a smaller shop on site. Thus it could claim to be the first purpose-built Department Store in the world. The word department store had not been invented at that time and thus it was called the "<a3_0><b8_0>Monster House<b8_0/><a3_0/>". The store was completely destroyed in the <a4_0><b9_0>1916<b9_0/><a4_0/> Easter Rising, but reopened in 1922.
